e> Re: Basic Game Play</span><hr size=1> there is a building that builds 3 different heroes for each race, there are little monsters called creeps around the map, you kill the creep and the level of your hero goes up<br><br>it sounds complicated but it's really not. <p><center><img src=http://www.sifl-n-olly.com/graphics/nav/corner.gif ></center><center><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=220223>gosu's bluebie gear.</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#999999><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uzhugruk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zhugruk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>cyb4r? ^_~</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/11/02 7:51:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/fsullonzektothecorefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Basic Game Play</span><hr size=1> You can also pick up magic items like weapons that give damage bonuses, potions, scrolls, etc etc from the creeps that your hero can carry.<br><br>Basically, if you choose not to level up a hero, your opponent will have a distinct advantage in combat over you because heroes get all kinds of abilities as they go up in level. Every time your hero goes up in level, it is similar to the way an AA point is used in EQ; You spend it to upgrade an ability of choice for that hero.<br><br>Each hero has a unique set of abilities and there are heroes that use AoE augmentation for offense/defense for your whole raiding force. There are also a ton of other spells and direct combat things to use too.<br><br>Some of the creeps guard goblin merchant encampments which you can use to buy potions and make 3 different goblin units from (i.e. acts like another barracks but for the goblin units)<br><br>On a couple maps there is also a dragon roost that is guarded by some dragons. If you take a force and kill the dragons, you can produce 3 levels of dragons to fight for you (also works like a barracks)<br><br>That's it in a nutshell. <p><br><br><br><br><center><a href="http://www.dabashiniggles.com"><img src="http://www.x-entertainment.com/pics/cool1.jpg"></a><p><b><big>Anton the Virtuoso<br>&lt;Nine&gt;</big></b></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#999999><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/upsu199.showPublicProfile?language=EN>psu199</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poop butt</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/11/02 7:59:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/fsullonzektothecorefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Basic Game Play</span><hr size=1> Beast<br><br>Hadmadinn Proudfoot <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#999999><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uveninkssz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Veninks SZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>hoe bag</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/11/02 8:17:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/fsullonzektothecorefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.battle.net/war3/images/orc/units/portraits/farseer.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Basic Game Play</span><hr size=1> for heroes? getting them level 6+ is pretty crucial.  each heroes' ultimate is invaluable. <p><img src=http://www.battle.net/war3/images/orc/units/animations/farseer.gif> - Rip off</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#999999><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uveninkssz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Veninks SZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>hoe bag</span><br>